<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-8514] Kafka clients should not include Scala&apos;s Java 8 compatibility lib</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-8514</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The work with&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-8305&quot; title=&quot;AdminClient should support creating topics with default partitions and replication factor&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-8305&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-8305&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; brought in &quot;org.scala-lang.modules:scala-java8-compat_2.12&quot; &lt;br/&gt;
as dependency of the client lib. This will give users from Scala an extra headache as it would need to be excluded when working with another Scala version.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Instead, it should be moved to be a dependency of &lt;b&gt;&quot;core&quot;&lt;/b&gt; for the convenience of converting Java and Scala Option instances.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/commit/8e161580b859b2fcd54c59625e232b99f3bb48d0#diff-c197962302397baf3a4cc36463dce5eaR942&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/commit/8e161580b859b2fcd54c59625e232b99f3bb48d0#diff-c197962302397baf3a4cc36463dce5eaR942&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
